{"user_message": {"title": "ADR-0004 · Citation-Format Validator — Architecture Decision (ai-paralegal)", "content": "## ADR-0004 · Citation-format validator as a pre-lookup stage in the citations gate\n\n**Status:** Proposed · **Date:** 2026-05-27 · written to `docs/adr/ADR-0004-citation-format-validator.md`\n\n### Context\nThe \"0 hallucinated cites\" promise is enforced by `verifyCitations()` (`src/lib/citations/verify.ts`) — the sole producer of branded `VerifiedLegalText` (CULTURE.md §3). But this gate verifies **existence**, not **format**, and has a structural blind spot:\n\n- **Detection is regex-gated.** `parseCitations()` finds cites only via `CITATION_REGEX`. A cite a human recognizes but that misses the strict regex (`410 US 113` without periods, `410 U.S. 113 at 115`, transposed reporter) is **neither `found` nor `failed`** — it gets branded and shown to the user un-flagged.\n- **Statutes/rules are explicitly skipped today.** `discovery/actions.ts` notes FRCP/TRCP cites \"pass through\" — there's no positive format check for `42 U.S.C. § 1983` or state codes.\n- **No format vocabulary.** `CitationError` has only `verification_failed` and `lookup_unavailable` — no way to express \"present but malformed,\" so `CitationAuditDrawer.tsx` can't render it.\n\nThe requested feature is **not** a duplicate of `verifyCitations()`: existence answers \"does this case exist?\"; format answers \"is it well-formed, and did we even recognize it?\" — the gate's current blind spot.\n\n### Decision\nAdd a format-validation stage **inside** the citations module, run **before** the existence lookup, and extend the gate's error vocabulary — **no** sibling utility, no new outbound surface. CULTURE.md §3 stays intact.\n\n1. New `validateCitationFormat(text)` in `src/lib/citations/`, run by `verifyCitations()` before `runLookup()`; classifies each reference-shaped span `well_formed | malformed | unrecognized` for both case **and** statute/rule cites.\n2. Extend `CitationError` with a **`format_invalid`** variant + `FormatIssue` reason.\n3. Close the silent-pass-through gap with a *loose* citation-like scanner — spans that look like cites but fail strict format are flagged, not ignored.\n4. Adopt CourtListener `normalized_citations` as canonical format authority; flag raw-vs-normalized drift (non-blocking).\n5. Add statute/rule grammar so they're classified, not skipped.\n\n**Modules that change:** `src/lib/citations/{types.ts, verify.ts}` (core); `src/features/demand-letter/actions.ts` + `src/features/discovery/actions.ts` (new error branch, compile-forced); `src/features/demand-letter/components/CitationAuditDrawer.tsx` (new flagged-format state).\n\n### Edge cases identified\nMalformed cites missing the strict regex (the core gap); statutes/procedural rules (`U.S.C. §`, state codes, FRCP); pincites & parallel cites; string cites; short forms (`id.`/`supra`); reporter spacing variants (`S. Ct.` vs `S.Ct.`); `lookup_unavailable` masking a malformed cite.\n\n### Consequences\n**Positive:** closes a demonstrable gap (malformed cites that brand clean today); zero new infra; consumers compile-error until they handle `format_invalid`; statutes become first-class. **Risks:** false positives from the loose scanner; scope creep toward a full Bluebook engine (kept scoped to reporters the firm emits); UNVERIFIED — static inspection only, no runtime/live-API confirmation.\n\n### Open question for downstream (Code Reviewer / Security Auditor / Docs Steward)\nShould `format_invalid` **hard-block** the draft or **warn-and-flag** for attorney judgment? **Recommendation:** hard-block `malformed`/`missing-components` (credibility-killers), warn-only on stylistic format-drift.\n\n---\n## Task breakdown — 8 tasks, 26 story points\n\n| # | Task | Pts |\n|---|------|-----|\n| 1 | Extend `CitationError` + add `FormatIssue` type (`types.ts`) | 2 |\n| 2 | Add statute/procedural-rule grammar; exclude from case lookup | 3 |\n| 3 | Implement `validateCitationFormat()`; wire as pre-lookup stage | 5 |\n| 4 | Loose citation-like scanner — close silent pass-through gap | 5 |\n| 5 | Adopt `normalized_citations` as format authority (drift note) | 3 |\n| 6 | Thread `format_invalid` through demand-letter + discovery actions | 2 |\n| 7 | Surface format failures in `CitationAuditDrawer.tsx` | 3 |\n| 8 | Tests — validator units + malformed-cite regression | 3 |\n\n```chart\nCore citations module (tasks 1-5): 18\nConsumers + UI (tasks 6-7): 5\nTests (task 8): 3\n```\n\nFull ADR persisted at `docs/adr/ADR-0004-citation-format-validator.md`. Builds on ADR-0002 (choke-points) and CULTURE.md §3. `architecture.analysis.completed` emitted for the delivery agent.", "content_type": "success", "priority": "normal"}}

