{"user_message": {"title": "Security Scan Report — ai-paralegal — 2026-05-27", "content": "# Security Scan Report — ai-paralegal\n**Date:** 2026-05-27 · **Scope:** full `src/` tree (64 source files), `package.json`/`package-lock.json`, env files · **Trigger:** post-review handoff (ADR-0004 citation-gate review)\n\n**Coverage:** All three phases completed — ✅ dependency audit (`npm audit`), ✅ secret detection, ✅ code-pattern analysis. No phase skipped. This is the **first scan** (persona memory empty), so no dedupe was needed; two findings below independently corroborate the code-review handoff.\n\n## Summary by severity\n| Severity | Count |\n|---|---|\n| Critical | 0 |\n| High | 2 |\n| Medium | 3 |\n| Low | 2 |\n\n---\n\n## 🔴 High\n\n### H-1 — No real authentication: hardcoded dev tenant grants attorney authority on every request\n**`src/lib/tenant.ts:55-63`** (consumed at `src/features/demand-letter/actions.ts:49,152`, `src/features/discovery/actions.ts:135`, `src/features/medical-records/actions.ts:91,159,303`, and all `src/app/**/page.tsx`).\n**Risk (auth bypass + tenant-isolation collapse):** Every server action resolves its identity from `getDevTenantContext()`, which returns a fixed context — tenant `suarez-law`, attorney `atty-suarez` **with sign-off authority**. There is no session/auth check anywhere. If this reaches a deployed environment, any unauthenticated caller can draft *and sign* legal artifacts as a real attorney, and all data is forced into one tenant — defeating the branded-`TenantContext` isolation the codebase otherwise enforces. Erring high per auth policy; **escalates to Critical if deployed to production.**\n**Fix:** Replace `getDevTenantContext()` with a real `getServerSession()`-backed resolver before any non-dev deploy. Add a hard guard that throws at startup if `NODE_ENV === \"production\"` and the dev seam is still active.\n\n### H-2 — Full privileged document sent to third-party CourtListener API\n**`src/lib/citations/verify.ts:142`** (`runCourtListenerLookup` → `fetch(COURTLISTENER_URL, { body: JSON.stringify({ text }) })`).\n**Risk (confidentiality / data egress, CWE-200):** When `COURTLISTENER_API_TOKEN` is set, the gate POSTs the **entire** AI-drafted document (`raw`) — plaintiff name, medical chronology, settlement valuation, privileged matter facts — to `courtlistener.com` on every verification. This is an attorney-client-privilege egress surface not covered by ADR-0003 (which hardened only the AI call site). *Corroborates the code-review handoff.* Currently dormant in dev (`COURTLISTENER_DISABLED=true`), but live the moment a token is configured.\n**Fix:** Transmit only citation-shaped spans (you already capture `start`/`end` in `parseCitations`) instead of the full document, **or** gate the live lookup behind explicit per-tenant opt-in documented in the DPA. Add to ADR-0004 scope or a sibling security ADR.\n\n---\n\n## 🟡 Medium\n\n### M-1 — `postcss < 8.5.10` XSS (CWE-79, CVSS 6.1), pulled transitively by `next`\n**`package.json` / `package-lock.json`** (`node_modules/next/node_modules/postcss`). Confirmed by `npm audit`: 2 moderate advisories (`GHSA-qx2v-qp2m-jg93` — XSS via unescaped `` in CSS stringify output).\n**Fix:** Add a package override forcing `postcss >= 8.5.10`. ⚠️ Do **not** run `npm audit fix --force` — it proposes downgrading `next` to `9.3.3` (a destructive major rollback); pin postcss via `overrides` instead.\n\n### M-2 — Live Google API key in plaintext dev file\n**`.env.local:1`** — `GEMINI_API_KEY=AIzaSy…` (real `AIza`-format key; value redacted here).\n**Risk:** A working credential sits in plaintext in the workspace. *Mitigating:* verified **not** tracked by git and never committed (`.env*.local` is gitignored), so no VCS leak. Residual exposure is anyone with filesystem/workspace access.\n**Fix:** Rotate the key (any credential that has left a developer's machine should be considered burned), confirm it is a restricted/low-privilege key, and keep it out of any shared image or backup.\n\n### M-3 — Citation gate silently passes through documents with zero detected cites\n**`src/lib/citations/verify.ts:240-251`** — when `found.length === 0`, the raw text is branded `VerifiedLegalText` via `_unsafeBrand(raw)` and shipped unflagged.\n**Risk (integrity of the \"0 hallucinated cites\" guarantee):** A citation the regex/CourtListener miss is neither verified nor failed — it ships unverified. *Corroborates the code-review handoff / the ADR-0004 gap.*\n**Fix:** Implement `validateCitationFormat()` as the pre-lookup stage per ADR-0004; an unrecognized/malformed span must **block** branding, not pass through.\n\n---\n\n## 🟢 Low\n\n### L-1 — Raw failed-citation text written to logs\n**`src/lib/citations/verify.ts:261`** → `failedCites: failed.map(c => c.raw)`, emitted via `logEvent` (`src/lib/logging/log.ts:18`, `console.log` → Cloud Logging).\n**Risk:** Document-derived strings reach the log sink. Citation strings are low-sensitivity, but ensure the Cloud Logging sink is access-controlled and not exported to lower-trust destinations. **Fix:** Confirm log-sink IAM; consider truncating/redacting if these spans can carry surrounding party text.\n\n### L-2 — Permissive heuristic fallback when CourtListener token absent\n**`src/lib/citations/verify.ts:199-207`** — `isCourtListenerEnabled()` falling false routes to `runHeuristicLookup`, which `.env.example` itself warns is \"too permissive for real legal work.\"\n**Risk:** A misconfigured production deploy (no token) silently degrades citation verification to the weak heuristic with no operator signal. **Fix:** Fail closed (or emit a loud startup warning) when `NODE_ENV === \"production\"` and no token is configured.\n\n---\n\n*Findings capped per category for actionability. Dependency, secret, and pattern phases all completed — no coverage gaps. H-1 (auth) is the most urgent: it ships as a deploy-time foot-gun today.*", "content_type": "warning", "priority": "high"}}

